trend_summary: Across the series the suburb steadily infills: housing spreads into former woodland, and east-side logistics estates overtake fields. A new arterial road boosts connectivity, prompting clustered commercial growth. Green cover thins but parks persist. Expansion is incremental and low-rise, yielding a medium-density, predominantly suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Large logistics/warehouse complex on the eastern flank doubles in footprint, replacing farmland.
Vacant lots in the northwest and central areas filled with new residential subdivisions.
Construction of a northeast-to-southwest arterial road and associated junctions.
Central woodland patch fragmented by estate development and access roads.
Perimeter agricultural plots transition to mixed commercial and light-industrial uses.
